This is a programming challenge!
You will receive 3 variables for input :
- 1 : string = the number to convert,
- 2 : int = the actual numeric system,
- 3 : int = the numeric sytem to convert to
Your mission is to do a function that will convert the 1st parameter from the actual numeric system to the new numeric system
Numeric systems : binary (2), octal (8), decimal (10)
No standard C function allowed (means you have to code the converter in different bases by yourself)
letters will be in lowercase for hexadecimal cases

2 hours challenge

Bonus:
+50 for the fastest
+50 for the shortest code (you canÂ´t have both bonus)

The function will be prototyped as follows:
long int    ft_binary(int a, int b, int c);

Rendu:
File to turn in : ft_binary.c
Norminette mandatory
Program in C only
No tricks or traps : input will always be valid

Example
Input                                   Output
1111            2           10          15
34              10          8           42
